WEBVTT

1
00:02:15.455 --> 00:02:17.206
Keep going!

2
00:02:17.207 --> 00:02:19.208
Bring it on down!

3
00:02:19.209 --> 00:02:20.543
- That's it!
- Come on!

4
00:02:20.544 --> 00:02:22.044
- Keep moving!
- Back into it.

5
00:02:24.715 --> 00:02:26.132
Three more in here.

6
00:02:28.760 --> 00:02:30.721
Three more in there.

7
00:02:31.763 --> 00:02:32.889
You. go with them!

8
00:02:33.932 --> 00:02:35.392
Two more in here.

9
00:02:39.646 --> 00:02:40.939
Two more in here.

10
00:02:48.572 --> 00:02:50.574
You three. in this one.

11
00:02:52.409 --> 00:02:53.660
Oh. please. please.

12
00:02:54.870 --> 00:02:57.079
Our home. it's...
it's already crowded.

13
00:02:57.080 --> 00:02:59.749
There's 15.000 of us.

14
00:02:59.750 --> 00:03:01.168
Be glad you only got three.

15
00:03:04.254 --> 00:03:06.923
- Maybe crowded ain't so bad.
- Mind yourself.

16
00:03:08.175 --> 00:03:10.926
You don't like it.
go and carp to Lord Ormund.

17
00:03:10.927 --> 00:03:12.262
See what good it does you.

18
00:03:25.317 --> 00:03:29.487
It is only regarding
the lodging situation. my lord.

19
00:03:29.488 --> 00:03:32.114
You are unhappy with
your lodgings. Lord Footly?

20
00:03:32.115 --> 00:03:34.450
It is only that we are very fond
of our ancestral home.

21
00:03:34.451 --> 00:03:36.411
You are sleeping
in our bedchamber.

22
00:03:37.245 --> 00:03:39.664
You bent the knee to the pretender.
Rhaenyra Targaryen.

23
00:03:39.665 --> 00:03:41.666
did you not. Lady Footly?

24
00:03:41.667 --> 00:03:43.459
We did.

25
00:03:43.460 --> 00:03:44.877
Then mayhaps
I should remind you

26
00:03:44.878 --> 00:03:46.837
that the wage of treason
is death.

27
00:03:46.838 --> 00:03:48.381
We do not seek conflict.
my lord.

28
00:03:48.382 --> 00:03:50.800
Tumbleton has no battlements.

29
00:03:50.801 --> 00:03:52.510
Our people know only trade.

30
00:03:52.511 --> 00:03:55.346
We never thought to see war.

31
00:03:55.347 --> 00:03:57.306
So. you swore to her
out of fear.

32
00:03:57.307 --> 00:03:59.893
We swore because
she is the queen.

33
00:04:03.188 --> 00:04:04.690
Is she?

34
00:04:14.908 --> 00:04:17.160
Or is she a bitch
with a dragon?

35
00:04:21.373 --> 00:04:23.666
My purpose is to restore
the rightful line

36
00:04:23.667 --> 00:04:24.918
to the Iron Throne.

37
00:04:26.002 --> 00:04:28.505
It follows from that
that I must be well rested.

38
00:04:30.006 --> 00:04:34.344
It follows from that that I must have
acceptable lodgings.

39
00:04:35.262 --> 00:04:38.597
I will ensure that my men
remain on their best behavior

40
00:04:38.598 --> 00:04:40.183
whilst in your town.

41
00:04:42.227 --> 00:04:44.396
Provided. of course...

42
00:04:46.606 --> 00:04:48.858
...that you remain on yours.

43
00:04:48.859 --> 00:04:50.193
See them out.

44
00:04:52.779 --> 00:04:54.156
Don't.

45
00:04:54.740 --> 00:04:56.240
When dealing with those
beneath you.

46
00:04:56.241 --> 00:04:58.284
you must be fair. but firm.

47
00:04:58.285 --> 00:04:59.703
Yes. sire.

48
00:05:02.789 --> 00:05:04.039
My prince.

49
00:05:04.040 --> 00:05:06.375
My lord. a raven
from Storm's End

50
00:05:06.376 --> 00:05:09.087
carrying more excuses
from Lord Borros Baratheon.

51
00:05:16.344 --> 00:05:19.013
That lackwit sealed a marriage pact
between Prince Aemond

52
00:05:19.014 --> 00:05:21.974
and one of his horse-faced
daughters.

53
00:05:21.975 --> 00:05:23.934
And yet. where is he now?

54
00:05:23.935 --> 00:05:26.061
Send another raven
that he can understand.

55
00:05:26.062 --> 00:05:28.565
This one mayhaps with drawings
rather than letters.

56
00:05:34.362 --> 00:05:36.156
What word from Harrenhal?

57
00:05:38.366 --> 00:05:42.579
If Vhagar does not come.
our defenses will not hold.

58
00:05:48.376 --> 00:05:50.212
Do not be disheartened.
Daeron.

59
00:05:51.922 --> 00:05:53.590
Your brother will join us soon.

60
00:05:58.595 --> 00:06:01.138
<i>Why seize Tumbleton?</i>

61
00:06:01.139 --> 00:06:04.183
It's no stronghold.
It's a market town.

62
00:06:04.184 --> 00:06:07.436
Its lord is meek.
Its walls are poorly defended.

63
00:06:07.437 --> 00:06:09.814
Hightower may as well
paint a rondel on his chest.

64
00:06:09.815 --> 00:06:10.816
Why?

65
00:06:11.942 --> 00:06:14.110
Does he mean to somehow
win their support?

66
00:06:16.196 --> 00:06:19.114
He dares me
to rain fire down on a seat

67
00:06:19.115 --> 00:06:21.283
that raised my banner.

68
00:06:21.284 --> 00:06:23.661
And the realm would name me
"Maegor Returned."

69
00:06:23.662 --> 00:06:25.621
They'd rise up against me.

70
00:06:25.622 --> 00:06:28.290
And the same gods
who delivered me to the throne

71
00:06:28.291 --> 00:06:29.667
would rightly cast me down.

72
00:06:29.668 --> 00:06:32.378
If I may.

73
00:06:32.379 --> 00:06:34.296
Your Grace.
Prince Daemon's river host

74
00:06:34.297 --> 00:06:36.632
marches on King's Landing.

75
00:06:36.633 --> 00:06:39.009
Tumbleton is not much further.

76
00:06:39.010 --> 00:06:41.387
If his men were
to go there instead...

77
00:06:41.388 --> 00:06:44.390
Mm. it would not be bloodless.

78
00:06:44.391 --> 00:06:47.477
but it would be far more
merciful than sending dragons.

79
00:06:49.479 --> 00:06:51.146
We march on the town

80
00:06:51.147 --> 00:06:53.650
and root out the Hightowers
house to house.

81
00:06:55.652 --> 00:06:57.403
It's a good scheme.

82
00:06:57.404 --> 00:06:59.030
Send orders to Lord Tully.

83
00:07:00.991 --> 00:07:02.367
Uh. Orwyle?

84
00:07:03.952 --> 00:07:07.247
For as long as you remain
loyal and useful...

85
00:07:08.415 --> 00:07:10.499
you may take your place
at my council

86
00:07:10.500 --> 00:07:12.335
and retain the title
of Grand Maester.

87
00:07:16.214 --> 00:07:18.173
The castle's ravens
remain your charge.

88
00:07:18.174 --> 00:07:20.760
but the Lady Mysaria should be
kept informed of the comings and goings.

89
00:07:21.720 --> 00:07:22.721
Ah.

90
00:07:23.680 --> 00:07:26.683
Relics of a dead regime.

91
00:07:27.851 --> 00:07:29.518
Mm.

92
00:07:29.519 --> 00:07:32.271
It will take the Rivermen weeks
to reach Tumbleton.

93
00:07:32.272 --> 00:07:34.773
Let us send a dragon
to keep vigil.

94
00:07:34.774 --> 00:07:37.234
Ormund may have
the town under siege.

95
00:07:37.235 --> 00:07:40.279
but he shall not leave
except I remove him.

96
00:07:40.280 --> 00:07:45.075
In the meantime. we have.
uh. urgent matters at home.

97
00:07:45.076 --> 00:07:47.578
We have secured
some small store of oil

98
00:07:47.579 --> 00:07:49.372
- for the markets. but...
- Where is the Hand?

99
00:07:51.333 --> 00:07:54.210
Gods. this council's thin.

100
00:07:58.715 --> 00:08:00.383
Name a Master of Coin.

101
00:08:01.384 --> 00:08:04.970
The people will soon discover
our lacking resources.

102
00:08:04.971 --> 00:08:07.015
They can blame him.

103
00:08:11.436 --> 00:08:14.063
Investigate
Ser Torrhen Manderly.

104
00:08:14.064 --> 00:08:15.898
He's intrigued me.

105
00:08:15.899 --> 00:08:18.735
If he's fit. let the gold
be his concern as well as Daemon's.

106
00:08:20.403 --> 00:08:22.906
Mine shall be
Ormund Hightower.

107
00:08:26.576 --> 00:08:28.327
I know him as well as you.

108
00:08:28.328 --> 00:08:30.413
I... I doubt that.

109
00:08:31.414 --> 00:08:34.250
Viserys warded your son to him.
I've never met the man.

110
00:08:35.585 --> 00:08:39.922
I knew him very little.
a long time ago.

111
00:08:39.923 --> 00:08:42.800
After my father took me to court.
I rarely saw Oldtown.

112
00:08:42.801 --> 00:08:44.135
Tell me what you do know.

113
00:08:49.516 --> 00:08:51.935
He sees himself as a scholar.

114
00:08:53.061 --> 00:08:54.937
He studies the histories.

115
00:08:54.938 --> 00:08:58.190
he collects tapestries.
writes ballads.

116
00:08:58.191 --> 00:09:00.151
despises the ignorant
and uncouth.

117
00:09:01.569 --> 00:09:03.445
When we were young.
Gwayne thought him cruel.

118
00:09:03.446 --> 00:09:05.781
but Gwayne thought that of many.

119
00:09:05.782 --> 00:09:07.117
How is he with Daeron?

120
00:09:09.494 --> 00:09:11.704
Fatherly. I'm told.

121
00:09:11.705 --> 00:09:13.832
Daeron was only a babe
when he took him to ward.

122
00:09:14.833 --> 00:09:16.459
What is it?

123
00:09:17.210 --> 00:09:18.794
Oh. look at this.

124
00:09:18.795 --> 00:09:21.965
Did it pain you to have
to send your child away?

125
00:09:26.636 --> 00:09:28.346
It was my choice.

126
00:09:29.305 --> 00:09:30.306
Why?

127
00:09:34.477 --> 00:09:38.690
I bore Viserys
three Targaryens.

128
00:09:40.191 --> 00:09:41.985
But with the last. my last...

129
00:09:43.194 --> 00:09:45.155
I wanted him to be a Hightower.

130
00:09:47.073 --> 00:09:49.158
In truth. I'm glad
I waged that battle.

131
00:09:49.159 --> 00:09:51.327
seeing now what came
of our other sons.

132
00:09:51.870 --> 00:09:55.331
Perhaps sending Daeron away
was my truest act of motherhood.

133
00:09:58.251 --> 00:09:59.877
Though I do not know
now what fate

134
00:09:59.878 --> 00:10:01.379
that choice has consigned him.

135
00:10:09.512 --> 00:10:11.765
You know I would
have spared him.

136
00:10:21.566 --> 00:10:24.027
He has a sensitivity
to odors.

137
00:10:25.820 --> 00:10:26.863
Ormund.

138
00:10:28.573 --> 00:10:29.908
A very strong one.

139
00:10:32.660 --> 00:10:35.037
My Lord Hand.
the queen has requested

140
00:10:35.038 --> 00:10:36.872
your presence
at her small council.

141
00:10:36.873 --> 00:10:39.583
I'm her Hand.
not her mouth.

142
00:10:39.584 --> 00:10:41.877
Leave the talking to those
who relish it.

143
00:10:41.878 --> 00:10:43.378
Shall I return
with this message?

144
00:10:43.379 --> 00:10:44.838
That you refuse the queen?

145
00:10:44.839 --> 00:10:47.549
Rather that I serve
more effectively.

146
00:10:47.550 --> 00:10:50.219
Her strength lies
in dragons now.

147
00:10:50.220 --> 00:10:52.388
She has less need
of a man of the sea.

148
00:10:54.599 --> 00:10:57.726
But my son shall attend her
in my stead.

149
00:10:57.727 --> 00:10:59.395
You certainly look the part.

150
00:11:00.897 --> 00:11:03.023
I am not a creature
of the court.

151
00:11:03.024 --> 00:11:04.775
I don't know what I'm doing.

152
00:11:04.776 --> 00:11:07.112
There is great opportunity
for you there.

153
00:11:08.780 --> 00:11:10.864
I cannot give you legitimacy.

154
00:11:10.865 --> 00:11:13.409
but I can give you the chance
to better yourself.

155
00:11:18.414 --> 00:11:22.001
Anger is not something that can
be ended with a blade. my lord.

156
00:11:26.589 --> 00:11:27.799
Move out!

157
00:11:39.144 --> 00:11:40.311
Come on!

158
00:12:36.326 --> 00:12:38.244
My boy.

159
00:12:39.370 --> 00:12:40.663
I'm here.

160
00:12:42.665 --> 00:12:43.833
I'm here.

161
00:12:47.921 --> 00:12:50.048
It's a penny
to touch the dragon.

162
00:12:52.008 --> 00:12:54.760
Nothing's free
in these woods.

163
00:12:54.761 --> 00:12:57.054
He can sit the saddle
for a halfgroat.

164
00:12:57.055 --> 00:12:58.680
Touch will suffice.

165
00:12:58.681 --> 00:13:00.058
- Mm.
- Thank you.

166
00:13:04.354 --> 00:13:07.105
We seek shelter.

167
00:13:07.106 --> 00:13:09.066
Which way to Rook's Rest?

168
00:13:09.067 --> 00:13:11.193
He's got both hands on him.

169
00:13:11.194 --> 00:13:12.528
That's two touches.

170
00:13:30.922 --> 00:13:32.799
What's wrong with your leg?

171
00:13:37.053 --> 00:13:41.140
You can kill a man of the Faith
for a few pennies. if you wish.

172
00:13:42.725 --> 00:13:45.394
Though I doubt the gods
would look kindly upon it.

173
00:13:45.395 --> 00:13:47.479
You don't look like a septon.

174
00:13:47.480 --> 00:13:48.940
He's alive.

175
00:13:53.403 --> 00:13:56.071
I know it.
He's alive. he must be.

176
00:13:56.072 --> 00:13:58.156
- Sunfyre.
- There. there. Gregor.

177
00:13:58.157 --> 00:13:59.741
Wake up. Sunfyre.
I'm here.

178
00:13:59.742 --> 00:14:01.910
Let us trouble these
good folk no further. hm?

179
00:14:01.911 --> 00:14:03.996
Wake up. Sunfyre.
I'm here.

180
00:14:03.997 --> 00:14:05.290
Simple.

181
00:14:08.584 --> 00:14:10.460
What's he saying?

182
00:14:10.461 --> 00:14:12.671
Sunfyre. come back to me.

183
00:14:12.672 --> 00:14:14.881
Wake up. I'm here.
I know you're in there.

184
00:14:14.882 --> 00:14:17.676
We must tarry no longer.
The danger is great.

185
00:14:17.677 --> 00:14:19.970
I am very sorry.

186
00:14:19.971 --> 00:14:22.307
but you must accept
what is before you.

187
00:14:25.101 --> 00:14:26.351
Wake up.

188
00:14:26.352 --> 00:14:29.022
You wanted to see him.
you've seen him.

189
00:14:30.315 --> 00:14:32.941
- He's dead.
- No.

190
00:14:32.942 --> 00:14:34.985
Will you stay and rot with him?

191
00:14:36.529 --> 00:14:39.324
Will you get up and live?

192
00:15:55.608 --> 00:15:57.151
Are you lost?

193
00:16:02.031 --> 00:16:03.699
Where is the castellan?

194
00:16:06.369 --> 00:16:07.703
Slain.

195
00:16:08.538 --> 00:16:09.914
He who succeeds him then.

196
00:16:11.874 --> 00:16:13.458
Slain.

197
00:16:13.459 --> 00:16:15.420
And the one
who succeeds him as well.

198
00:16:16.879 --> 00:16:18.297
And who are you?

199
00:16:19.215 --> 00:16:21.425
A steward. of a sort.

200
00:16:21.426 --> 00:16:24.052
It's the best you can do
at the moment.

201
00:16:24.053 --> 00:16:25.805
This is the Hand of the King.

202
00:16:26.597 --> 00:16:28.099
We seek the Prince Aemond.

203
00:16:30.059 --> 00:16:32.061
As I'm sure do many.

204
00:16:35.565 --> 00:16:37.899
He was meant
to meet us here.

205
00:16:37.900 --> 00:16:39.151
If you know where he is.

206
00:16:39.152 --> 00:16:41.611
I'd advise you
to be forthcoming.

207
00:16:45.741 --> 00:16:47.201
He was here.

208
00:16:48.244 --> 00:16:51.496
He seized the castle after
Prince Daemon abandoned it.

209
00:16:51.497 --> 00:16:54.249
but when he learned that
Rhaenyra took King's Landing.

210
00:16:54.250 --> 00:16:57.086
- he and his dragon fled.
- W-When Rhaenyra took King's Landing?

211
00:17:02.967 --> 00:17:04.260
Oh. my.

212
00:17:05.511 --> 00:17:06.971
Oh. you didn't know.

213
00:17:12.935 --> 00:17:14.936
We've scoured the area.
my Lord Hand.

214
00:17:14.937 --> 00:17:17.189
There is sign
of a large dragon nest

215
00:17:17.190 --> 00:17:18.608
but it has been abandoned.

216
00:17:19.609 --> 00:17:22.195
Prince Aemond
may indeed have fled.

217
00:17:32.788 --> 00:17:34.498
King's Landing has fallen.

218
00:17:34.499 --> 00:17:37.709
Aegon is dead. our queens
are both in chains.

219
00:17:37.710 --> 00:17:40.003
and we are here alone

220
00:17:40.004 --> 00:17:42.173
with a meager army
and no dragon.

221
00:17:44.133 --> 00:17:45.968
We have the enemy
just where we want them.

222
00:17:48.513 --> 00:17:50.180
Aemond would not desert me.

223
00:17:50.181 --> 00:17:52.975
And yet he's not here. is he?

224
00:17:55.019 --> 00:17:56.771
Let us send a raven
to Tumbleton.

225
00:17:57.688 --> 00:17:59.814
Alert my cousin of this news

226
00:17:59.815 --> 00:18:02.359
and our intent
to join our strength to his.

227
00:18:02.360 --> 00:18:04.194
Ormund is a stiff-necked
windbag.

228
00:18:04.195 --> 00:18:05.654
but he's neither
craven nor stupid.

229
00:18:05.655 --> 00:18:07.990
He will have
some canny plot afoot.

230
00:18:11.327 --> 00:18:12.411
No.

231
00:18:18.167 --> 00:18:21.128
The game is played.
Ser Criston. and it is lost.

232
00:18:22.129 --> 00:18:24.089
What possible profit
is there in pursuing it?

233
00:18:28.844 --> 00:18:31.930
You noble ilk conceive this
all a great game. don't you?

234
00:18:31.931 --> 00:18:34.599
To win. to lose.
go home to a feather bed.

235
00:18:36.686 --> 00:18:39.020
I was a foot soldier.
Did you know that?

236
00:18:39.021 --> 00:18:40.522
Steward's son.

237
00:18:40.523 --> 00:18:43.358
All my father had was at
the pleasure of Lord Dondarrion.

238
00:18:43.359 --> 00:18:45.736
When his favor failed.
all we had melted away.

239
00:18:49.031 --> 00:18:50.908
My father died of sorrow.

240
00:18:51.867 --> 00:18:53.869
There is no home
for one like me.

241
00:18:56.539 --> 00:18:58.541
Not while Rhaenyra
sits the throne.

242
00:19:01.877 --> 00:19:03.421
Our task is simple.

243
00:19:04.797 --> 00:19:06.631
Keep the river scum
from reaching King's Landing.

244
00:19:06.632 --> 00:19:08.425
Give Ormund time
to swell his ranks.

245
00:19:08.426 --> 00:19:10.802
Their army is ten times
our size.

246
00:19:10.803 --> 00:19:12.053
Twenty.

247
00:19:12.054 --> 00:19:13.723
But let us attack it...

248
00:19:14.557 --> 00:19:16.559
as the scorpion does the ox.

249
00:19:19.353 --> 00:19:22.897
Let us become wraiths
with fear as our standard.

250
00:19:22.898 --> 00:19:24.441
Strike from the quiet
and the darkness.

251
00:19:24.442 --> 00:19:26.485
Our fight will not be clean.
but it will be pure.

252
00:19:28.321 --> 00:19:29.572
We'll be man-to-man.

253
00:19:32.617 --> 00:19:34.410
And it will be free
from dragons.

254
00:19:39.665 --> 00:19:42.251
- Ser Edgar!
- We'll delay them at most.

255
00:19:44.587 --> 00:19:47.088
- It will not change their course.
- Perhaps not.

256
00:19:47.089 --> 00:19:49.382
But it is as you said.
Ser Gwayne.

257
00:19:49.383 --> 00:19:52.928
We must cling to our honor.
lest we become beasts ourselves.

258
00:20:18.037 --> 00:20:19.537
Who goes there?

259
00:20:19.538 --> 00:20:20.997
Alyn of Hull.

260
00:20:20.998 --> 00:20:22.958
I'll see him. Come.

261
00:20:24.960 --> 00:20:27.128
Your Grace.

262
00:20:27.129 --> 00:20:30.006
Lord Corlys has ridden out
by the Dragon Gate

263
00:20:30.007 --> 00:20:32.510
to hunt the Triarchy raiders
that plague our trade.

264
00:20:34.470 --> 00:20:36.722
He has able men who could
lead that campaign.

265
00:20:38.224 --> 00:20:42.144
While his queen struggles
to restore a broken kingdom.

266
00:20:45.981 --> 00:20:47.983
Your Grace. uh. if I may.

267
00:20:49.527 --> 00:20:52.904
My lord father has lost much

268
00:20:52.905 --> 00:20:55.157
and found himself thwarted.

269
00:20:56.117 --> 00:20:59.995
A fight is mayhaps
what he needs.

270
00:21:02.415 --> 00:21:03.874
Hm.

271
00:21:06.335 --> 00:21:07.670
Oh.

272
00:21:08.713 --> 00:21:10.046
My father's life's work.

273
00:21:10.047 --> 00:21:12.800
a recreation of the seat
of Old Valyria.

274
00:21:14.510 --> 00:21:16.721
A reminder to him.
I think. that. um...

275
00:21:18.806 --> 00:21:20.725
even great dynasties fall.

276
00:21:21.851 --> 00:21:24.270
That the crown should
never rest easy on his head.

277
00:21:26.355 --> 00:21:29.691
There were those who whispered
that my father was weak.

278
00:21:29.692 --> 00:21:32.861
But. um.
seeing through his eyes.

279
00:21:32.862 --> 00:21:34.863
I can only marvel

280
00:21:34.864 --> 00:21:36.866
at how he kept it
all in balance for so long.

281
00:21:38.367 --> 00:21:41.202
Fathers have
a maddening capacity

282
00:21:41.203 --> 00:21:44.038
to at once inspire and incense.

283
00:21:44.039 --> 00:21:46.124
Don't you think?

284
00:21:48.544 --> 00:21:50.296
Gods. they are incessant.

285
00:21:52.214 --> 00:21:54.759
And thanks to Aegon.
all the rat catchers are dead.

286
00:21:56.218 --> 00:21:58.137
On board ship. we kept cats.

287
00:22:00.556 --> 00:22:03.601
Steel yourself.

288
00:22:04.935 --> 00:22:08.105
We must guard our intents
whilst I quietly

289
00:22:09.648 --> 00:22:12.025
investigate hiring a ship.

290
00:22:12.026 --> 00:22:14.903
This is Cole's garrison.
They owe allegiance to me.

291
00:22:14.904 --> 00:22:16.530
This is no garrison.

292
00:22:17.531 --> 00:22:20.409
You must presume these men hold
allegiance only to themselves.

293
00:22:27.249 --> 00:22:29.168
We cannot tarry here long.

294
00:23:01.116 --> 00:23:03.869
Good day. friend.
We seek food and shelter.

295
00:23:05.955 --> 00:23:08.998
Like many here gathered.
we are the dispossessed of the war.

296
00:23:08.999 --> 00:23:11.001
You Riverfolk?

297
00:23:12.670 --> 00:23:16.173
I fucking hate Riverfolk.

298
00:23:16.841 --> 00:23:19.217
We hail from Sharp Point.

299
00:23:19.218 --> 00:23:20.970
Prince Aemond burned it
to the ground.

300
00:23:22.471 --> 00:23:23.889
W-w-with his d...

301
00:23:27.810 --> 00:23:30.312
- How'd you get out?
- We nearly didn't.

302
00:23:33.190 --> 00:23:34.984
As you can see.

303
00:23:36.694 --> 00:23:38.320
Hm.

304
00:23:46.912 --> 00:23:49.163
Well...

305
00:23:49.164 --> 00:23:51.207
We're too many.

306
00:23:51.208 --> 00:23:52.585
Fuck off.

307
00:23:53.836 --> 00:23:55.337
I have some coin.

308
00:24:09.977 --> 00:24:13.354
You can earn a tent
if you're ready to work.

309
00:24:13.355 --> 00:24:14.731
Have you got a trade?

310
00:24:14.732 --> 00:24:16.399
I have some knowledge
of herbs.

311
00:24:16.400 --> 00:24:18.860
and. uh. I can read a little.

312
00:24:18.861 --> 00:24:20.029
Mm.

313
00:24:23.198 --> 00:24:24.782
Maybe you'll be useful.

314
00:24:24.783 --> 00:24:27.201
I have the command
around here.

315
00:24:27.202 --> 00:24:30.788
Oh. that much
is clear. my lord.

316
00:24:30.789 --> 00:24:32.458
Tangletongue
works the latrines.

317
00:24:33.751 --> 00:24:36.337
Collects piss for the tanners.
shit for the farmers.

318
00:24:37.880 --> 00:24:39.923
This one can help him.

319
00:24:39.924 --> 00:24:41.382
Separate buckets.

320
00:24:41.383 --> 00:24:44.218
Mix it up. they won't pay.

321
00:24:44.219 --> 00:24:47.305
I won't touch
the fucking latrines...

322
00:24:47.306 --> 00:24:49.390
J-Just do as they say.
Gregor.

323
00:24:49.391 --> 00:24:51.184
- For now. hm?
- I can read just as well as he can.

324
00:24:51.185 --> 00:24:53.561
Tangletongue and Mangleface.

325
00:24:58.067 --> 00:24:59.901
- You'll be good together.
- I-It's not bad...

326
00:24:59.902 --> 00:25:01.654
- Don't fucking touch me.
- ...once you're used to it. brother.

327
00:25:03.405 --> 00:25:04.907
Come on.

328
00:25:07.451 --> 00:25:09.160
Come on.

329
00:25:09.161 --> 00:25:11.454
Fuck off!

330
00:25:19.755 --> 00:25:21.631
I think we'll have
a nice time here tonight.

331
00:25:21.632 --> 00:25:26.094
We'll make merry tonight.
It'll be better than Honeyholt.

332
00:25:36.480 --> 00:25:38.774
Wait.

333
00:25:45.781 --> 00:25:48.200
I need to inspect the goods.

334
00:25:56.667 --> 00:25:58.794
Go and fetch
some rosemary.

335
00:26:05.134 --> 00:26:06.635
Come on.

336
00:26:13.142 --> 00:26:15.393
Don't touch her!
Take your hands off of her!

337
00:26:25.320 --> 00:26:26.863
Get them out of here!
Get them out!

338
00:26:26.864 --> 00:26:29.533
Get your hands off my brother.
you Hightower...

339
00:26:38.000 --> 00:26:39.752
Ser Hugh Hammer. Your Grace.

340
00:26:41.378 --> 00:26:43.171
Ser Hugh. I assure you.

341
00:26:43.172 --> 00:26:45.924
when there is news of a house.
you will be sent for.

342
00:26:47.468 --> 00:26:50.928
I understand that Ser Ulf
is to be sent to Tumbleton.

343
00:26:50.929 --> 00:26:53.514
- He is.
- If it pleases Your Grace.

344
00:26:53.515 --> 00:26:55.893
I offer to take the watch
on Vermithor.

345
00:26:58.020 --> 00:27:00.229
Your wife is at Tumbleton.
is she not?

346
00:27:00.230 --> 00:27:01.814
Ser Ulf has no stake
in the matter.

347
00:27:01.815 --> 00:27:03.358
Send me. because I do.

348
00:27:04.359 --> 00:27:07.071
I will not tire of watching
when one I love is below.

349
00:27:10.783 --> 00:27:12.241
Take it in turn between you.

350
00:27:12.242 --> 00:27:14.702
Keep watch on the town
and on each other.

351
00:27:14.703 --> 00:27:16.329
You may take the first post.

352
00:27:16.330 --> 00:27:18.040
See that Ulf is alerted
to the plan.

353
00:27:20.000 --> 00:27:21.418
Your Grace.

354
00:27:29.551 --> 00:27:31.428
Disgusting.

355
00:27:35.390 --> 00:27:37.059
What's it say?

356
00:27:40.437 --> 00:27:41.980
"Queen of Bastards."

357
00:27:43.190 --> 00:27:46.485
Hightower loyalists trying
to fight a war they lost.

358
00:27:53.242 --> 00:27:55.910
So. he has returned.

359
00:27:59.414 --> 00:28:01.249
- Come on!
- Come on.

360
00:28:01.250 --> 00:28:03.292
- Ah! Good evening. ser!
- Hey!

361
00:28:03.293 --> 00:28:06.838
Ulf. the Dragonlord!
Hey. hey.

362
00:28:06.839 --> 00:28:08.589
More god than man.

363
00:28:08.590 --> 00:28:12.009
Hey. will you honor your friends
with a round of drinks. my lord?

364
00:28:12.010 --> 00:28:14.220
The price keeps rising.
we can't keep up.

365
00:28:14.221 --> 00:28:16.097
- Tell him.
- For everyone.

366
00:28:16.098 --> 00:28:17.765
Hear that?

367
00:28:17.766 --> 00:28:21.937
Drinks for everyone!

368
00:28:25.440 --> 00:28:27.358
- He broke my arm.
- That one broke my nose.

369
00:28:27.359 --> 00:28:29.152
- He attacked my sister.
- You call yourself soldiers. This is a disgrace.

370
00:28:29.153 --> 00:28:30.779
- The children are terrified.
- What is this?

371
00:28:32.489 --> 00:28:34.657
You said your men
were honorable.

372
00:28:34.658 --> 00:28:35.993
This one has sinned.

373
00:28:39.121 --> 00:28:41.289
I was billeted
at the smithy. my lord.

374
00:28:41.290 --> 00:28:44.125
But the smith didn't like it.

375
00:28:44.126 --> 00:28:46.503
Mayhaps he resents
the imposition.

376
00:28:47.546 --> 00:28:49.673
Or mayhaps he is loyal
to Rhaenyra.

377
00:28:50.632 --> 00:28:51.966
But he struck me.

378
00:28:51.967 --> 00:28:53.968
My lord.
Now. if it please you.

379
00:28:53.969 --> 00:28:55.428
we bear you no ill will.

380
00:28:55.429 --> 00:28:57.889
But this man went
to ravish my sister

381
00:28:57.890 --> 00:29:00.683
and then broke my wife's arm
when she tried to stop him.

382
00:29:00.684 --> 00:29:02.476
She is a weaver.

383
00:29:02.477 --> 00:29:04.313
We need what little she earns.

384
00:29:05.480 --> 00:29:07.815
- Is this true?
- No. my lord.

385
00:29:07.816 --> 00:29:09.400
- Liar!
- Look at this woman's arm.

386
00:29:09.401 --> 00:29:11.402
- She attacked me.
- Is there no safety

387
00:29:11.403 --> 00:29:12.820
- in our houses anymore?
- She called me a cunt!

388
00:29:12.821 --> 00:29:14.489
I will have calm.

389
00:29:18.744 --> 00:29:21.412
- What is your name?
- Garrick. my lord.

390
00:29:21.413 --> 00:29:22.830
of Whitegrove.

391
00:29:22.831 --> 00:29:24.833
Garrick of Whitegrove.

392
00:29:25.918 --> 00:29:27.794
You have violated guest right.

393
00:29:28.503 --> 00:29:30.504
You have debauched yourself
upon a woman

394
00:29:30.505 --> 00:29:32.173
and injured another.

395
00:29:32.174 --> 00:29:34.217
Your punishment
will fit your crime.

396
00:29:34.218 --> 00:29:35.843
You will be gelded.

397
00:29:35.844 --> 00:29:39.180
And you will have
your own arm broken.

398
00:29:39.181 --> 00:29:40.431
You may remain in my service.

399
00:29:40.432 --> 00:29:42.600
but trespass again.
and you will hang.

400
00:29:42.601 --> 00:29:45.186
My lord. I have a wife.

401
00:29:45.187 --> 00:29:47.438
Oh! My lord!

402
00:29:47.439 --> 00:29:48.898
- Come on!
- No!

403
00:29:48.899 --> 00:29:51.360
See them home.
Have a maester tend to their wounds.

404
00:29:52.402 --> 00:29:53.612
No!

405
00:29:54.613 --> 00:29:55.864
My lord!

406
00:29:57.282 --> 00:30:00.535
We must keep a firm grip.
Tensions are high.

407
00:30:01.536 --> 00:30:04.705
Lawlessness and disorder
claw at our gates.

408
00:30:04.706 --> 00:30:05.958
Yes. sire.

409
00:30:15.842 --> 00:30:17.301
<i>I wish to see
all correspondence</i>

410
00:30:17.302 --> 00:30:19.387
between the Red Keep
and Ormund Hightower

411
00:30:19.388 --> 00:30:20.722
since my father's death.

412
00:30:21.431 --> 00:30:22.557
Your Grace.

413
00:30:25.560 --> 00:30:28.145
How much control
do the Hightowers

414
00:30:28.146 --> 00:30:29.939
exert over the Faith?

415
00:30:29.940 --> 00:30:34.068
Well. they endowed the building
of the Starry Sept

416
00:30:34.069 --> 00:30:36.237
and Oldtown was their seat for.

417
00:30:36.238 --> 00:30:39.156
well. centuries before
the Conquest.

418
00:30:39.157 --> 00:30:41.909
The Seven are as intrinsic
to the Hightower fabric

419
00:30:41.910 --> 00:30:44.996
as. well. dragons are
to House Targaryen.

420
00:30:44.997 --> 00:30:46.914
But control. I think not.

421
00:30:46.915 --> 00:30:49.960
The Faith is too proud
to allow such influence.

422
00:30:51.920 --> 00:30:54.506
The. uh. the High Septon
has refused to anoint me.

423
00:30:56.758 --> 00:31:00.137
The Faith clings tightly
to its separate powers.

424
00:31:03.098 --> 00:31:07.352
If I may be so bold
to ask Your Grace...

425
00:31:08.270 --> 00:31:09.687
does it matter?

426
00:31:09.688 --> 00:31:11.939
- Wh...
- Your Grace sits the throne.

427
00:31:11.940 --> 00:31:15.026
Your people have welcomed
you back as a liberator.

428
00:31:15.027 --> 00:31:16.569
Your dragons rule the skies.

429
00:31:16.570 --> 00:31:19.281
Are these not symbols
of power enough?

430
00:31:20.657 --> 00:31:23.242
Perhaps I could remove him.

431
00:31:23.243 --> 00:31:25.953
The monarch has ever had
some influence

432
00:31:25.954 --> 00:31:27.955
in the... the naming
of the High Septon.

433
00:31:27.956 --> 00:31:30.958
but to remove him altogether
would surely...

434
00:31:30.959 --> 00:31:33.962
incite the Faith.
and therefore the faithful.

435
00:31:36.131 --> 00:31:38.467
Unless you were
considering a more. uh...

436
00:31:40.635 --> 00:31:42.304
permanent removal.

437
00:31:44.306 --> 00:31:46.182
I never thought you
so bloodthirsty. Orwyle.

438
00:31:46.183 --> 00:31:48.225
- Ah.
- Rather impressed.

439
00:31:48.226 --> 00:31:49.810
Alas. no.

440
00:31:49.811 --> 00:31:51.854
Bring Ormund's letters
once you have collated them.

441
00:31:51.855 --> 00:31:55.566
There's been no word from
Prince Daemon on his progress?

442
00:31:55.567 --> 00:31:57.319
None as yet. Your Grace.

443
00:32:03.158 --> 00:32:04.492
I had thought never to see you

444
00:32:04.493 --> 00:32:06.994
in the Vale again.
Prince Daemon.

445
00:32:06.995 --> 00:32:09.915
What after the tragic death
of your first wife.

446
00:32:11.458 --> 00:32:14.251
And yet I receive raven after raven
from my bannermen

447
00:32:14.252 --> 00:32:17.171
informing me of your progress
throughout my domain.

448
00:32:17.172 --> 00:32:18.547
Hm.

449
00:32:18.548 --> 00:32:21.051
Time heals even
the deepest of wounds.

450
00:32:23.095 --> 00:32:25.972
I am most delighted
to return. my lady.

451
00:32:28.350 --> 00:32:32.853
And who could ever fail to be
charmed by your... warmth.

452
00:32:32.854 --> 00:32:34.647
But I mustn't tarry.

453
00:32:34.648 --> 00:32:37.858
You promised the crown men
in return for a dragon.

454
00:32:37.859 --> 00:32:40.195
Now. you had your dragon.
yet we have no men.

455
00:32:42.197 --> 00:32:44.407
I should send babes.

456
00:32:44.408 --> 00:32:45.991
Prince Joffrey's dragon
was years away

457
00:32:45.992 --> 00:32:47.910
from being large enough
to defend the Vale.

458
00:32:47.911 --> 00:32:49.621
and Rhaenyra took
even that away.

459
00:32:50.539 --> 00:32:52.373
A less forbearing person

460
00:32:52.374 --> 00:32:54.375
might have seen
the crown's offering as an insult.

461
00:32:54.376 --> 00:32:57.211
- A pledge is a pledge.
- It was my understanding

462
00:32:57.212 --> 00:32:59.296
that the war was won.
my prince.

463
00:32:59.297 --> 00:33:02.717
What need does she have
of more soldiers?

464
00:33:04.386 --> 00:33:05.595
In truth...

465
00:33:06.805 --> 00:33:09.598
I have not come for men.
I've come for gold.

466
00:33:09.599 --> 00:33:11.725
Huh. so your coffers are empty?

467
00:33:11.726 --> 00:33:13.185
The work of Hightower treachery.

468
00:33:13.186 --> 00:33:15.020
But perhaps a generous
offering of coin

469
00:33:15.021 --> 00:33:16.565
would demonstrate your...

470
00:33:17.732 --> 00:33:19.942
fealty to the crown.

471
00:33:19.943 --> 00:33:23.571
Prince Daemon Targaryen.
standing in my high hall.

472
00:33:23.572 --> 00:33:25.740
a beggar with a tin cup.

473
00:33:27.325 --> 00:33:29.243
I never thought I'd live
to see such a sight.

474
00:33:29.244 --> 00:33:31.245
A gift of gold
would offer you the benefit

475
00:33:31.246 --> 00:33:32.831
of my speedy departure.

476
00:33:38.336 --> 00:33:39.753
Very well.

477
00:33:45.760 --> 00:33:48.180
Hey!

478
00:33:54.978 --> 00:33:56.271
Hey!

479
00:35:10.345 --> 00:35:11.972
Reveal yourself!

480
00:35:36.705 --> 00:35:38.582
Rhaena.

481
00:35:57.976 --> 00:36:00.060
<i>- Lykiri!
- Daor.</i>

482
00:36:00.061 --> 00:36:01.562
<i>Lykiri.</i>

483
00:36:11.531 --> 00:36:13.783
What have you done to yourself?

484
00:36:19.164 --> 00:36:20.915
How?

485
00:36:23.585 --> 00:36:25.085
I fed him sheep.

486
00:36:28.882 --> 00:36:31.259
Rhaenyra believes this dragon
and his rider are the reason...

487
00:36:33.595 --> 00:36:35.263
Jace is dead.

488
00:36:39.601 --> 00:36:41.894
- I wanted only to help.
- No.

489
00:36:41.895 --> 00:36:44.689
To show her... to show you
I... I never intended...

490
00:36:46.483 --> 00:36:49.110
Does she suffer?

491
00:36:51.321 --> 00:36:53.197
Jeyne Arryn knows you're here.

492
00:36:53.198 --> 00:36:55.074
You were meant to accompany
my sons to Pentos.

493
00:36:55.075 --> 00:36:56.700
They are well attended.
They will be safe.

494
00:36:56.701 --> 00:36:58.952
- You swore to be their guardian.
- And do what?

495
00:37:01.164 --> 00:37:03.291
Teach them to be ladies
of the realm?

496
00:37:04.459 --> 00:37:06.293
I would be of no use there.

497
00:37:06.294 --> 00:37:08.338
Just as I was of no use here.

498
00:37:11.966 --> 00:37:14.843
If you go now to where
you are meant to be.

499
00:37:14.844 --> 00:37:16.053
Rhaenyra need not know.

500
00:37:16.054 --> 00:37:18.180
We will find a ship.
Leave the dragon behind.

501
00:37:18.181 --> 00:37:20.641
I will not leave him.

502
00:37:20.642 --> 00:37:21.892
He's not like the others.
Rhaena.

503
00:37:21.893 --> 00:37:23.644
He is wild.
He cannot be trusted.

504
00:37:23.645 --> 00:37:25.980
He is mine.
He is a part of me.

505
00:37:27.649 --> 00:37:29.359
I have been alone all my life.

506
00:37:31.319 --> 00:37:33.737
A Targaryen without a dragon.

507
00:37:33.738 --> 00:37:36.657
Disregarded. or... or worse.

508
00:37:36.658 --> 00:37:37.992
Pitied.

509
00:37:39.577 --> 00:37:41.370
Can you yourself
say you ever gave me

510
00:37:41.371 --> 00:37:42.871
more than a passing thought?

511
00:37:42.872 --> 00:37:44.999
Rhaena. the unfortunate.

512
00:37:46.543 --> 00:37:48.837
Rhaena. the least
among your children.

513
00:37:52.507 --> 00:37:54.216
Come back with me. then.
to King's Landing.

514
00:37:54.217 --> 00:37:55.844
- No.
- We will...

515
00:37:57.137 --> 00:37:59.513
speak to her together.
We will tell her it was a mistake.

516
00:37:59.514 --> 00:38:01.515
How can I ever stand
before her again

517
00:38:01.516 --> 00:38:03.685
after what I have done?

518
00:38:04.686 --> 00:38:06.812
No. I can never return.

519
00:38:06.813 --> 00:38:10.607
I will remain here.
alone and in exile.

520
00:38:10.608 --> 00:38:13.069
- That is my penance.
- She will hunt you down.

521
00:38:14.028 --> 00:38:15.362
Is hunting now.

522
00:38:15.363 --> 00:38:18.116
Let them grieve me
and think me lost to sea.

523
00:38:21.244 --> 00:38:23.203
Unless you betray me.

524
00:38:23.204 --> 00:38:25.372
You ask me to deceive her.
That is betrayal.

525
00:38:25.373 --> 00:38:28.960
I have asked you nothing.
Father. in all my life.

526
00:38:31.129 --> 00:38:32.880
I ask this one thing
of you now.

527
00:38:32.881 --> 00:38:34.631
Rhaena. Rhaena.

528
00:38:34.632 --> 00:38:35.884
Rhaena!

529
00:38:37.927 --> 00:38:38.928
Rhaena!

530
00:38:55.403 --> 00:38:57.405
Shh!

531
00:39:40.782 --> 00:39:43.700
A raven just arrived
from Harrenhal. my lord.

532
00:39:43.701 --> 00:39:46.287
It bears the Hightower seal.

533
00:40:10.520 --> 00:40:11.980
Get out.

534
00:40:12.730 --> 00:40:14.481
My prince?

535
00:40:14.482 --> 00:40:16.317
Out. Now.

536
00:40:28.496 --> 00:40:31.915
Useless craven coward!

537
00:40:31.916 --> 00:40:34.042
Cunt!

538
00:40:36.546 --> 00:40:38.881
Cunt! Cunt!

539
00:40:38.882 --> 00:40:40.841
Cunt!

540
00:41:09.412 --> 00:41:11.706
Your Uncle Gwayne
has sent word.

541
00:41:13.791 --> 00:41:15.709
It seems your brother Aemond

542
00:41:15.710 --> 00:41:18.046
will not be joining us
after all.

543
00:41:20.632 --> 00:41:22.258
Is...

544
00:41:23.551 --> 00:41:25.428
Gwayne coming to Tumbleton?

545
00:41:28.139 --> 00:41:30.058
We must alter our scheme.

546
00:41:34.562 --> 00:41:37.106
<i>Ser Otto wrote
diligently to Ormund.</i>

547
00:41:37.899 --> 00:41:39.566
Naught was returned.

548
00:41:39.567 --> 00:41:42.069
Are you sure
there's been no error?

549
00:41:42.070 --> 00:41:43.071
Nothing?

550
00:41:45.740 --> 00:41:47.241
What am I to make of this?

551
00:41:48.618 --> 00:41:51.536
I suppose only
that Lord Ormund

552
00:41:51.537 --> 00:41:54.916
ruled Oldtown
as a kingdom unto itself.

553
00:41:55.875 --> 00:41:56.834
Mm.

554
00:42:14.769 --> 00:42:18.105
Ser Ulf White is still
without. Your Grace.

555
00:42:18.106 --> 00:42:19.273
Oh. uh...

556
00:42:20.483 --> 00:42:21.484
Come.

557
00:42:23.945 --> 00:42:25.029
Your Grace.

558
00:42:26.614 --> 00:42:29.199
I'm honored
to be in your service

559
00:42:29.200 --> 00:42:32.452
and to have sworn my life
to your cause.

560
00:42:32.453 --> 00:42:33.496
Yes. I'm sure.

561
00:42:34.497 --> 00:42:37.624
- What is it. then?
- Oh. I... I wondered

562
00:42:37.625 --> 00:42:41.086
whether. as Your Grace's
humble servant.

563
00:42:41.087 --> 00:42:44.507
I might petition
for your favor... er. favors.

564
00:42:45.299 --> 00:42:46.800
Speak them.

565
00:42:46.801 --> 00:42:50.053
For a man named Mujja.

566
00:42:50.054 --> 00:42:54.141
a smallholding outside Rosby

567
00:42:54.142 --> 00:42:56.727
and exemption from taxes.
thanking Your Grace.

568
00:42:56.728 --> 00:42:59.062
And for a fellow named Cley.

569
00:42:59.063 --> 00:43:02.649
a pardon for various
small crimes.

570
00:43:02.650 --> 00:43:04.651
We don't have to go into that.
and passage to Lys...

571
00:43:04.652 --> 00:43:06.319
These favors
are not in your name.

572
00:43:06.320 --> 00:43:08.156
No. no. Your Grace.

573
00:43:09.991 --> 00:43:11.409
They're for allies...

574
00:43:12.744 --> 00:43:14.828
from a tavern
I frequent... ed.

575
00:43:14.829 --> 00:43:17.331
- frequented previously.
- A tavern.

576
00:43:19.542 --> 00:43:23.712
And if an agent
of the Hightowers

577
00:43:23.713 --> 00:43:26.006
knifes you in your belly
as you fill it with ale?

578
00:43:26.007 --> 00:43:28.551
No. it's not that sort of place.
Besides...

579
00:43:31.012 --> 00:43:34.014
- It's my belly.
- Oh. but it's not.

580
00:43:34.015 --> 00:43:37.267
No. you belong now
to the crown.

581
00:43:37.268 --> 00:43:40.020
Should something
befall you or your belly.

582
00:43:40.021 --> 00:43:41.855
I suffer the loss of a dragon

583
00:43:41.856 --> 00:43:43.982
and the unity of the realm
is threatened.

584
00:43:43.983 --> 00:43:47.194
No. you shall frequent
taverns no longer.

585
00:43:47.195 --> 00:43:48.737
What?

586
00:43:48.738 --> 00:43:50.989
Well. I'm afraid you'll
have to find your...

587
00:43:50.990 --> 00:43:53.366
your beer within the walls
of the Red Keep.

588
00:43:53.367 --> 00:43:56.119
where you will remain...

589
00:43:56.120 --> 00:43:58.205
except when you are escorted
to the Dragonpit

590
00:43:58.206 --> 00:43:59.457
for duty at Tumbleton.

591
00:44:00.792 --> 00:44:02.877
If that is all. you may go.

592
00:44:12.845 --> 00:44:14.097
They protest you.

593
00:44:15.264 --> 00:44:18.226
You know.
out there in the city.

594
00:44:19.227 --> 00:44:22.146
I've seen vile words
painted on walls.

595
00:44:23.940 --> 00:44:25.108
They say...

596
00:44:26.734 --> 00:44:28.152
"Queen of Bastards."

597
00:44:31.906 --> 00:44:34.241
The work. I am sure.

598
00:44:34.242 --> 00:44:36.827
of some of your
misguided subjects

599
00:44:36.828 --> 00:44:39.997
who mistakenly believe
their queen to be unkind.

600
00:44:44.919 --> 00:44:46.170
Your Grace.

601
00:45:04.814 --> 00:45:06.940
Can you send word
to Ser Luthor?

602
00:45:06.941 --> 00:45:10.443
Have his gold cloaks look
for any seditious markings

603
00:45:10.444 --> 00:45:12.321
on the streets of the city.
remove them...

604
00:45:13.656 --> 00:45:15.241
and find those responsible.

605
00:45:15.950 --> 00:45:17.284
And bring them to you.
Your Grace?

606
00:45:17.285 --> 00:45:19.954
Just make it cease. please.

607
00:45:40.850 --> 00:45:43.895
There's a Braavosi cog sailing
from Duskendale in a few days.

608
00:45:44.812 --> 00:45:47.189
- I think I can find us fresh horses.
- I'm the fucking king.

609
00:45:47.190 --> 00:45:48.941
If they knew I walked among them.

610
00:45:49.859 --> 00:45:52.819
Even were you to be believed.
Rhaenyra sits the throne.

611
00:45:52.820 --> 00:45:54.571
And you have no dragon.

612
00:45:54.572 --> 00:45:56.991
She did us a favor
by declaring you dead.

613
00:45:59.493 --> 00:46:00.577
I'm dead?

614
00:46:00.578 --> 00:46:02.079
Slain by your brother Aemond.

615
00:46:03.372 --> 00:46:05.165
Is that what they say?

616
00:46:05.166 --> 00:46:06.833
Mm.

617
00:46:06.834 --> 00:46:07.959
I'll fucking kill him.

618
00:46:07.960 --> 00:46:10.046
- I'll fucking kill her. the s...
- In time.

619
00:46:12.256 --> 00:46:14.841
There's much to be learned
from the chatter in this camp.

620
00:46:14.842 --> 00:46:18.596
Anonymity is a boon for us.

621
00:46:19.347 --> 00:46:23.684
It will ensure that your
eventual resurrection...

622
00:46:26.187 --> 00:46:28.189
becomes the stuff
of song and legend.

623
00:46:32.109 --> 00:46:33.527
Have something to eat.

624
00:46:42.286 --> 00:46:43.870
None left for us.

625
00:46:43.871 --> 00:46:45.248
Happens sometimes. but...

626
00:46:46.207 --> 00:46:48.876
We'll get some tomorrow.

627
00:46:49.585 --> 00:46:51.045
Tomorrow?

628
00:46:54.048 --> 00:46:56.216
I'll not stand for this.

629
00:46:56.217 --> 00:46:58.010
Outrage!

630
00:46:59.303 --> 00:47:01.597
Is this how you rule?
Running out of food?

631
00:47:04.392 --> 00:47:06.060
Answer me!

632
00:47:07.061 --> 00:47:09.813
Sit down
before I make you.

633
00:47:09.814 --> 00:47:11.189
Who do you think
you're talking to?

634
00:47:11.190 --> 00:47:12.984
I'll have your fucking tongue.
you insolent ape.

635
00:47:13.901 --> 00:47:15.277
- Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.
- Please.

636
00:47:15.278 --> 00:47:19.072
And I'll gut you
like a fish. cunt.

637
00:47:19.073 --> 00:47:21.909
Let's... let's not be hasty.

638
00:47:26.247 --> 00:47:28.081
On your knees.

639
00:47:28.082 --> 00:47:29.333
if you want to live.

640
00:47:54.150 --> 00:47:55.776
Kiss my feet.

641
00:47:57.945 --> 00:48:00.322
- I take it back.
- Or die.

642
00:48:00.323 --> 00:48:01.490
I don't care which.

643
00:48:03.951 --> 00:48:05.619
But you will call me...

644
00:48:06.370 --> 00:48:08.705
- "my lord."
- Janos.

645
00:48:08.706 --> 00:48:10.124
You as well?

646
00:48:37.068 --> 00:48:39.194
The inquisitions were thorough.

647
00:48:39.195 --> 00:48:41.404
We should be assured
that wherever they might be.

648
00:48:41.405 --> 00:48:43.323
the crown's holdings...

649
00:48:43.324 --> 00:48:46.077
- are no longer in...
- I bring justice.

650
00:48:50.831 --> 00:48:52.333
I bring vengeance.

651
00:48:53.918 --> 00:48:55.294
I also bring gold.

652
00:48:57.671 --> 00:49:01.049
- What is this?
- The one who rode Sheepstealer.

653
00:49:01.050 --> 00:49:05.388
Along with 10.000 golden dragons
from Lady Jeyne Arryn.

654
00:49:07.640 --> 00:49:09.600
Anything from
her bannermen in the Vale?

655
00:49:10.726 --> 00:49:13.228
We still await some response
from the great houses.

656
00:49:13.229 --> 00:49:16.106
And the Iron Bank has not
answered our request for a loan.

657
00:49:16.107 --> 00:49:18.149
Would you please explain
who that is?

658
00:49:18.150 --> 00:49:21.861
Ser Torrhen Manderly. my prince.
the new Master of Coin.

659
00:49:21.862 --> 00:49:24.114
What little there is
to be a master of.

660
00:49:24.115 --> 00:49:26.741
Well. I'll wager you think you're clever.
don't you. Manderly?

661
00:49:26.742 --> 00:49:28.076
- Well...
- You should know

662
00:49:28.077 --> 00:49:29.620
I'm the clever one around here.

663
00:49:31.664 --> 00:49:33.748
- Say no more.
- What small quantity

664
00:49:33.749 --> 00:49:37.252
of gold Daemon has found
must go to ease the deprivations

665
00:49:37.253 --> 00:49:39.254
- of the smallfolk.
- The City Watch is stretched far too thin.

666
00:49:39.255 --> 00:49:40.755
Our soldiers need to be paid

667
00:49:40.756 --> 00:49:43.299
and more recruited besides.
else there will be bedlam.

668
00:49:43.300 --> 00:49:44.717
- Your Grace...
- Bedlam is assured

669
00:49:44.718 --> 00:49:46.302
if the people feel the crown
ignores their anger.

670
00:49:46.303 --> 00:49:48.638
Has anyone considered a tax?

671
00:49:48.639 --> 00:49:50.307
Clear the room.

672
00:50:07.158 --> 00:50:08.325
What is this?

673
00:50:10.202 --> 00:50:11.453
The queen's justice.

674
00:50:11.454 --> 00:50:12.788
Who is he?

675
00:50:13.831 --> 00:50:16.249
And how did he come
to claim a wild dragon?

676
00:50:16.250 --> 00:50:18.626
Was he alone. or is...

677
00:50:18.627 --> 00:50:21.212
is he allied to Aemond
or to Ormund?

678
00:50:21.213 --> 00:50:22.755
I desired
the very same answers.

679
00:50:22.756 --> 00:50:24.507
but a dragon is not
a precise instrument.

680
00:50:24.508 --> 00:50:27.177
What of Sheepstealer?

681
00:50:27.178 --> 00:50:29.345
Fled. Riderless.

682
00:50:29.346 --> 00:50:31.264
It is an act of madness
to claim a wild dragon.

683
00:50:31.265 --> 00:50:32.808
We are not like to see it again.

684
00:50:39.607 --> 00:50:42.776
I wanted to see him.

685
00:50:46.947 --> 00:50:50.993
I wanted to look on the one
who killed my son.

686
00:50:55.289 --> 00:50:56.916
To punish him yourself?

687
00:50:59.460 --> 00:51:01.670
But do you think
that would end your grief?

688
00:51:02.630 --> 00:51:04.256
I have served your interest.

689
00:51:15.643 --> 00:51:19.063
The gold you brought will
provide alms for the smallfolk.

690
00:51:20.272 --> 00:51:23.150
The City Watch trusts you.
You will entreat them to be patient.

691
00:51:24.485 --> 00:51:26.487
The crown will honor its debt...

692
00:51:27.488 --> 00:51:28.822
a little longer.

693
00:51:35.162 --> 00:51:36.330
I suppose...

694
00:51:37.665 --> 00:51:39.333
I should thank you.

695
00:51:48.551 --> 00:51:52.345
When what you've wrought
comes falling down about her ears.

696
00:51:52.346 --> 00:51:55.015
she'll return to her senses.

697
00:51:55.724 --> 00:51:57.309
Whose head is that?

698
00:52:37.057 --> 00:52:40.393
I have dispatched good men
to see your father's remains

699
00:52:40.394 --> 00:52:41.937
delivered to Oldtown.

700
00:52:50.321 --> 00:52:51.780
Viserys would have wished it.

701
00:52:54.617 --> 00:52:55.826
Thank you.

702
00:53:17.765 --> 00:53:19.016
Here.

703
00:53:31.779 --> 00:53:33.280
Helaena.

704
00:53:38.786 --> 00:53:40.828
Clear the streets.

705
00:53:40.829 --> 00:53:42.330
Clear the streets!

706
00:53:42.331 --> 00:53:44.667
Observe the curfew!

707
00:53:47.795 --> 00:53:49.213
All indoors!

708
00:53:51.131 --> 00:53:52.633
Clear the street!

709
00:53:55.135 --> 00:53:57.845
Stay home or hang!

710
00:53:57.846 --> 00:53:59.848
Dragon!

711
00:54:00.182 --> 00:54:01.308
Dragon!

712
00:54:26.834 --> 00:54:29.919
Open your doors by order of the queen.

713
00:54:29.920 --> 00:54:32.172
Here! Here!

714
00:54:33.340 --> 00:54:34.757
- With me.
- Up here.

715
00:54:34.758 --> 00:54:36.843
Get them out of their home!

716
00:54:36.844 --> 00:54:38.011
Who did this?

717
00:54:39.179 --> 00:54:41.139
Which traitor
stained these walls?

718
00:54:41.140 --> 00:54:42.890
Find the hand that
stained these walls.

719
00:54:42.891 --> 00:54:44.350
Scrub. Scrub!

720
00:54:46.854 --> 00:54:48.021
Bring them out!

721
00:55:09.251 --> 00:55:11.711
- Has he confessed?
- Not yet.

722
00:55:11.712 --> 00:55:14.089
I haven't done anything.
Please.

723
00:55:15.549 --> 00:55:16.717
Please.

724
00:55:17.843 --> 00:55:21.137
Patience. my girl.

725
00:55:21.138 --> 00:55:23.390
It won't be long before
we can fly again.

726
00:55:27.186 --> 00:55:29.645
I have warned you
against indulging in affection

727
00:55:29.646 --> 00:55:31.105
for that beast.

728
00:55:33.400 --> 00:55:34.651
<i>Lykiri.</i>

729
00:55:39.907 --> 00:55:41.492
I know.

730
00:55:51.251 --> 00:55:52.669
You are a good boy.

731
00:55:54.338 --> 00:55:57.007
You speak kindly
and you say your prayers.

732
00:55:58.175 --> 00:56:00.009
I have raised you
in the light of the Seven.

733
00:56:00.010 --> 00:56:01.887
and the Father smiles upon you.

734
00:56:03.847 --> 00:56:05.933
But there is a taint
in your blood.

735
00:56:07.434 --> 00:56:10.269
The Targaryens
are a savage race.

736
00:56:10.270 --> 00:56:12.439
poor in intellect.
but rich in cunning.

737
00:56:14.191 --> 00:56:17.109
With dark spells.
they created abominations

738
00:56:17.110 --> 00:56:18.946
to subdue what was rightly ours.

739
00:56:22.908 --> 00:56:24.535
We are the superior men.

740
00:56:25.619 --> 00:56:27.954
But against that...

741
00:56:29.706 --> 00:56:31.124
...we could not stand.

742
00:56:39.675 --> 00:56:42.386
The gods have put you
to divine purpose. my boy.

743
00:56:43.428 --> 00:56:45.472
What purpose. sire?

744
00:56:46.807 --> 00:56:50.519
The brutes raise a woman
to the Iron Throne.

745
00:56:51.353 --> 00:56:52.562
A desecration!

746
00:56:52.563 --> 00:56:55.315
Where is reason?
Where is propriety?

747
00:56:56.316 --> 00:56:58.485
It was a blessing that you
came to ward in Oldtown.

748
00:56:59.486 --> 00:57:01.905
Your brothers are lost.
but you...

749
00:57:02.906 --> 00:57:05.032
remain a Hightower.

750
00:57:05.033 --> 00:57:07.451
raised in the shadow
of the Citadel.

751
00:57:07.452 --> 00:57:09.872
in the light of the Starry Sept.

752
00:57:14.877 --> 00:57:15.878
Now...

753
00:57:17.045 --> 00:57:18.672
you must be king.

754
00:57:23.844 --> 00:57:26.178
You would not wish. surely.

755
00:57:26.179 --> 00:57:28.681
for me to turn cloak
against my brothers.

756
00:57:28.682 --> 00:57:31.017
You will restore
our ancient order.

757
00:57:31.018 --> 00:57:33.937
Victory will be ours.
It is the will of the gods.

758
00:57:36.189 --> 00:57:37.733
I thought you let him go.

759
00:57:38.692 --> 00:57:40.443
A righteous king
must demonstrate

760
00:57:40.444 --> 00:57:42.570
he upholds many virtues.

761
00:57:42.571 --> 00:57:44.281
Honor. wisdom.

762
00:57:45.365 --> 00:57:48.367
- Justice. - He only acted when
our man attacked a woman.

763
00:57:48.368 --> 00:57:50.161
He laid hands on a Hightower.

764
00:57:50.162 --> 00:57:53.456
That soldier is an extension
of you. of the crown.

765
00:57:53.457 --> 00:57:55.041
Justice must be done.

766
00:57:55.042 --> 00:57:57.251
Is not mercy a kingly virtue?

767
00:57:57.252 --> 00:57:59.587
That sounds like something
your father would say.

768
00:58:03.884 --> 00:58:05.218
I'm sorry.

769
00:58:27.199 --> 00:58:30.077
I have risked much
and more to raise you up.

770
00:58:31.912 --> 00:58:33.956
Surely. you do not wish
to disappoint me.

771
00:58:50.931 --> 00:58:52.682
My lord.

772
00:58:52.683 --> 00:58:55.267
My lord. please. Please.

773
00:58:55.268 --> 00:58:57.812
No. please. I beg you.

774
00:58:57.813 --> 00:58:59.189
